      • unixTime

        public static long unixTime(java.time.LocalDateTime time)
        Computes the UNIX time (or Epoch time) of the specified LocalDateTime. Computes the number of seconds that has elapsed since Thursday 1. of January 1970 at 00:00:00 UTC.
        Parameters:
        time - The LocalDateTime to compute unix time from.
        Returns:
        Returns the amount of seconds since 01/01/1970 00:00:00 UTC.

      • readableDate

        public static java.lang.String readableDate(java.time.LocalDateTime time)

        Parameters:

        Returns:
        Returns a human readable date and time String.

      • doubleDigits

        public static java.lang.String doubleDigits(int number)
        Converts an integer between 0 and 9 to double digit String representation. I.e. 5 -> "05". Any number passed outside of this range is returned as a String representation.
        Parameters:
        number - The number to convert.
        Returns:
        Returns a double digit String representation of the passed integer.
